FC Bayern beat Bayer Leverkusen 2-0 on Tuesday night to advance to the Champions League quarter-finals. Harry Kane handed Bayern the lead after half-time and Alphonso Davies rounded off the scoreline as FCB won 5-0 on aggregate.
Munich lined up with Jonas Urbig in goal and Konrad Laimer, Dayot Upamecano, Minjae Kim and Davies in defence. Joshua Kimmich and Leon Goretzka anchored a midfield featuring Michael Olise, Jamal Musiala and Kingsley Coman, with Kane up front. Josip Stanišić came on for Laimer at half-time, with Serge Gnabry, Hiroki Ito, João Palhinha and Thomas Müller taking over from Coman, Olise, Goretzka and Kane in the second half.
